Program: Outlook
Title: Life after killing an intruder
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p016tkmm
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 2 Apr 2013
Matthew Bannister speaks to Dr Johnny Slaughter about the aftermath of killing someone who had broken into his Baltimore home. German photographer Michael Najjar tells us about his plans to be the first artist in space. Also parents in prison - Burmese journalist Tin Mar Swe brought up her daughter in solitary confinement for seven years and Nepalese social worker Pushpa Basnet is a surrogate mum to scores of children whose mothers are behind bars. All that and your stories too, share them via outlook@bbc.com Picture: Outlook presenter, Matthew Bannister Show less